# CHANGELOG — bricklink-studio skill

Format: [vX.Y.Z] YYYY-MM-DD — Description
- Major (X): breaking restructure
- Minor (Y): new sub-skill or significant feature
- Patch (Z): fixes, renames, content updates

---

## [v1.3.0] 2026-04-05 — Knowledge base restructured by domain; Awesome LEGO ML expanded to individual entries
- knowledge/INDEX.md: full rewrite — domain-based directory with 30 entries across 8 categories + routing hints
- knowledge/part-recognition.md: NEW — Brickognize, RebrickNet, mobile apps, hierarchical 2-step, synthetic data protocol
- knowledge/assembly-planning.md: NEW — Graph Transformer ASP, LEGO manual→plan (ECCV 2022), Break&Make, robotic assembly (2023)
- knowledge/model-generation.md: NEW — 3D-to-Lego, LSculpt, Legolization, architectural gen, deep graph generative model, Stable Diffusion LEGO
- knowledge/datasets-rendering.md: NEW — BrickRenderer, Lego Renderer for ML (Blender), BrickRegistration, synthetic protocol, public datasets
- knowledge/spatial-reasoning.md: NEW — SRM (ICML 2025), SpaceTools/DIRL, Lambrecht paper, Awesome Spatial VLM, Awesome Multimodal SR
- knowledge/collections.md: NEW — meta resources: Awesome LEGO ML, Awesome Spatial VLM, Awesome LEGO (general)
- knowledge/repos.md + research.md: deprecated, content distributed to domain files

## [v1.2.0] 2026-04-05 — Knowledge base sub-skill with hierarchical index and access counting
- knowledge/INDEX.md: new entry point with ⚡ Hot cache, full directory, routing hints, and promotion protocol
- knowledge/algorithms.md: Voxelization, Legolization, Assembly Sequence Planning, Collision Detection
- knowledge/tools.md: LSculpt, LDraw standard, three.js LDraw loader, community resources
- knowledge/repos.md: 3D-to-Lego, Awesome LEGO ML, LDraw Visualizer, Awesome Spatial Intelligence, Awesome Multimodal Spatial Reasoning
- knowledge/research.md: SRM (ICML 2025), SpaceTools/DIRL, Lambrecht voxelization paper
- SKILL.md: knowledge added to routing table, compatibility matrix, sub-skill index

## [v1.1.0] 2026-04-05 — Instruction Maker workflow, full shortcuts, selection tools, anti-patterns
- gui-navigation/guide.md: Best Practices section (camera/nav, movement, selection, alignment, submodels, performance + NO AUTOSAVE warning)
- gui-navigation/guide.md: Instruction Maker full workflow (prepare → steps → page design → callouts → Buffer Exchange → BOM → export)
- gui-navigation/references/shortcuts.md: Full keyboard shortcut reference from official BrickLink Help Center (Building Mode + Instruction Maker)
- bom-export/guide.md: Export formats (CSV, Wanted List XML) and Custom Palette workflow
- learning/failed.md: 3 confirmed anti-patterns (layout corruption, snapping slowdown, Buffer Exchange drag bug)

## [v1.0.8] 2026-04-05 — Best practices: submodels, performance, WASD, Render Queue
- gui-navigation/references/submodels.md (NEW): Ctrl+G grouping, linked duplicates,
  Copy and Mirror, naming conventions, submodels in Instructions Maker
- gui-navigation/references/performance.md (NEW): snapping lag fix, Collision Detection toggle,
  viewport Render Quality setting, large model tips
- gui-navigation/references/shortcuts.md: WASD movement (no snap/collision), arrow rotation
  (90°/45°), T Movement Controls, F focus + Reset Origin
- render/references/settings.md: Render Queue workflow, Stud Logo toggle with use-case table

## [v1.0.7] 2026-04-05 — New sub-skill: render
- Added render/guide.md: Studio Photo Realistic render workflow, Blender path, common issues table
- Added render/references/settings.md: quality presets, resolution, background, lighting, performance tips
- SKILL.md: added render to compatibility matrix, routing logic, sub-skill index
- SKILL.md: fixed CHANGELOG path (meta/ → root) and build command

## [v1.0.6] 2026-04-05 — GUI improvements: screenshot strategy, overlap indicator, hotkeys
- gui-navigation/guide.md: area screenshot protocol with macOS shortcut variants and clipboard note
- gui-navigation/guide.md: visual indicator for overlapping/clipping bricks (contour outline)
- gui-navigation/guide.md: multi-action batching efficiency pattern with learn/record loop
- gui-navigation/references/shortcuts.md: full part movement (arrow keys, Page Up/Down),
  rotation, snapping, and precision placement via Properties

## [v1.0.5] 2026-04-05 — New references: .io format, pile workflow, Blender pipeline
- Added ldraw-format/references/io-format.md: .io ZIP structure, model.ldr vs lxfml distinction,
  Python code for reading/editing/analyzing .io files, git restore workflow
- Added gui-navigation/references/workflows.md: Part Replacement UI (Workflow 7),
  Random Pile of Parts (Workflow 8), Stud.io → Blender export (Workflow 9)
- Added gui-navigation/references/shortcuts.md: R/T part placement hotkeys
- GitHub repo: published to github.com/uncurrent/bricklink-studio-skill
- Added GitHub Actions: auto-build .skill on push, versioned releases on tag
- Added CONTRIBUTING with setup guide and learning cycle documentation
- Added LICENSE (MIT), moved skill files and CHANGELOG to repo root

